{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Pin down exact runtime behavior of the immutable-field guard with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fba32312d872acd18","f4550dc4ca20c669a"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"exact runtime behavior of the immutable-field guard"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":5,"blocking":0,"dropped":11,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":14,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","ran":true,"references":0,"resolved":0,"status":"pass"},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":14,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":13899,"file_impact":8,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":3,"edges":3,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":14,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"pass","verify_commands_linted":4,"verify_lint_abstained":4},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":3491,"ran":true,"status":"pass","worst_parent_child_pair_tokens":5709},"P9":{"applicable":false,"blocking":false,"file_impact":8,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":278.7,"llm_calls":23,"llm_ms":374964.3,"total_ms":375371.6,"verify_requests":19},"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":true,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["G3","G4","G6","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","F1","F4","G5","T12","T2","T4","T5e","T7"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the exact fallback behavior when `process_edit` encounters a field name in `_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS`: silent skip (current behavior generalized), warning log, or raised error; reconcile the 'skip' language in Architecture Decisions with the 'refuse' language in AC4.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py lines 492-504: `for field_name, new_value in fields.items(): if field_name not in state: continue ... state[field_name] = new_value`","Plan uses the word 'skip' (silent) while AC4 says processors 'refuse to overwrite' — these imply different behaviors (silent drop vs. active refusal/error)","No fallback behavior (warning, error, or silent drop) is specified for the case where an EDIT event supplies a value for an immutable field"],"finding":"The plan says `process_edit` will 'skip those names before its generic state assignment' for `_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS`, but the existing `process_edit` guard is `if field_name not in state: continue` (silently skips fields absent from state). Once `process_create` seeds `creation_channel` into state, the field IS in state, so the existing guard does NOT protect it — any EDIT event carrying `creation_channel` would overwrite it. The plan introduces `_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS` to fix this, but never specifies the fallback behavior when an EDIT event supplies the field: skip silently, log a warning, or raise an error.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fba32312d872acd18","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'define _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS = frozenset({\"creation_channel\", \"creation_channel_inferred\"}) and make process_edit skip those names before its generic state assignment'","norm_id":"n09b5c85fcb7f4cf5","priority":0.198,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An EDIT event with `creation_channel` in its fields dict silently loses the mutation (skip), which is correct but undetectable","An adversarial or buggy writer sends an EDIT with `creation_channel: cli` on a jira-origin ticket; the skip is silent and no audit trail records the attempted mutation"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Reconcile 'skip' (Architecture Decisions) with 'refuse' (AC4): state explicitly whether `process_edit` silently drops `creation_channel`/`creation_channel_inferred` fields from EDIT payloads or raises/logs an error, and update both sections to use the same verb.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Architecture Decisions: 'make process_edit skip those names before its generic state assignment'","AC4: 'process_edit plus every specialized mutation processor refuse to overwrite creation_channel or creation_channel_inferred after genesis'","These two verbs ('skip' vs 'refuse') describe different observable behaviors: silent discard vs. raised error/logged warning."],"finding":"The Architecture Decisions section says `process_edit` will 'skip those names before its generic state assignment', but AC4 says the processors will 'refuse to overwrite' — 'skip' (silent drop) and 'refuse' (error/exception) are materially different behaviors that affect observability, error handling, and downstream debugging. An executor cannot determine which behavior to implement without clarification.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4550dc4ca20c669a","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — '_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS' paragraph; Acceptance Criteria — AC4","norm_id":"nce5f5b5ed8522606","priority":0.132,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor implementing a silent skip passes the AC4 pytest test (field not overwritten) but leaves no trace when a caller mistakenly sends creation_channel in an EDIT payload.","An executor implementing a raise/log satisfies the 'refuse' language but could break callers that currently pass unknown keys."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"State the default in the Architecture Decisions paragraph: e.g., 'process_edit silently skips (drops without error) any key in _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS; callers supplying those keys receive no exception.' Then update AC4 to say 'silently ignore' rather than 'refuse to overwrite', or vice-versa if an explicit error is intended.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a pre-implementation empirical probe (e.g., a one-off script or fixture that samples real or representative anonymized legacy CREATE events) to validate that LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR and LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID exactly match all Jira-origin records and that no non-Jira records satisfy the three-signal predicate before finalizing the constants.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'require the exact three-signal Jira predicate and add near-miss negative cases' — prescribed tests are synthetic unit fixtures, not a measurement against real historical data","No spike, sample audit, or corpus measurement step is described anywhere in the plan","The plan asserts 'Missing/None signals or legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides intentionally project unknown' — this is a reasoning-based claim about real historical corpus shape","The predicate depends on exact literal constants whose validity against actual stored event logs is unverified"],"finding":"The three-signal historical Jira inference predicate (ticket_id prefix + exact LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR + exact LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID) is asserted safe against real historical records by reasoning alone, with no empirical probe or sample measurement against actual legacy event logs to confirm the predicate produces no false positives or unexpected false negatives at corpus scale.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f425e6ee4033fa6de","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Historical records without the field project jira only when all creation-stable signals agree…'; Risks — 'False historical attribution'","norm_id":"n34f45e11947917c4","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A legacy CREATE event was written with a variant author string (e.g., capitalization, whitespace, or a version-specific prefix) that does not match LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR exactly, causing a real Jira ticket to silently project unknown rather than jira","A non-Jira ticket coincidentally satisfies the three-signal predicate, producing a false jira attribution with creation_channel_inferred: true","The corpus contains both REBAR_AUTHOR and LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR variants for Jira-origin records, making the predicate coverage incomplete"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Before story e622 lands, run a read-only audit query (e.g., `rebar list --format ndjson | jq 'select(.event_type==\"CREATE\") | {id, author, env_id}'`) against a representative historical corpus and confirm the predicate covers all expected Jira-origin records with no unexpected matches. Record the sample result as a comment in _version.py alongside the constant definitions.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an ADR or CLAUDE.md section documenting the creation-channel provenance architectural decisions: the _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS reducer guard pattern, the late-import convention for cross-package constants, the closed-vocabulary rationale, and the inference-marker trust boundary.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["No ADR file (e.g., docs/adr/NNN-creation-channel-provenance.md) or CLAUDE.md section is mentioned anywhere in the plan","The plan introduces two novel patterns: a named immutability guard in the reducer and a deliberate cross-package late-import; both require future contributors to know the constraint and the rationale","Documentation ACs target only existing markdown files and make lint, not a new ADR or CLAUDE.md entry","'A novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc update' is the T5e documentation sub-check"],"finding":"The novel reducer guard pattern (_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS in process_edit) and the cross-component late-import convention (inbound_translate importing from rebar.reducer._version) are not captured in an ADR or CLAUDE.md entry — only existing documentation files are updated — leaving future contributors without a discoverable record of why these patterns were chosen and what constraints govern extending them.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4df1da3021d868ab","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — '_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS = frozenset…'; 'inbound_translate._event_meta performs the absolute package import … following the module's established late-import pattern'; Scope — documentation updates target docs/event-schema.md, docs/output-schemas.md, docs/concurrency.md","norm_id":"nea41a8a742d89bb3","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A future contributor adds a new field to process_edit without knowing the _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS guard pattern exists, inadvertently making a different CREATE-only field mutable","A future reconciler module author adds a top-level import from rebar.reducer._version without understanding the late-import contract, causing a circular import regression","The closed-vocabulary rationale is not discoverable, so a future ingress author adds an ad-hoc string channel value outside the validator"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Create docs/adr/NNN-creation-channel-provenance.md (or add a section to CLAUDE.md) capturing: (1) why creation_channel is CREATE/SNAPSHOT-only and how _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS enforces it, (2) the late-import pattern rationale in inbound_translate, (3) the closed enum extension policy, and (4) the inference marker's diagnostic-only (non-security) trust boundary. Reference this ADR from the relevant AC.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5714,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add ACs (or expand 568c AC5) to explicitly cover tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k 'legacy_snapshot or snapshot_only', matching the parent AC10 prove command exactly.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent AC10: 'Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k \"legacy_snapshot or snapshot_only or horizon or rebuild\" tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_snapshot.py'","Child 568c AC5: 'Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k \"rebuild or horizon or rollback_recovery\" tests/integration/test_concurrency_regression.py'","Child 568c AC3: 'Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_snapshot.py -k creation_channel' — different file, no 'legacy_snapshot or snapshot_only' selector","No sibling (6fe2 or e622) references test_creation_channel_compaction.py with these selectors","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Child 568c does not assign any AC to the 'legacy_snapshot' and 'snapshot_only' k-selectors within tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py, which parent AC10 explicitly requires. Child 568c AC5 covers -k 'rebuild or horizon or rollback_recovery' in that file, and AC3 covers test_reducer_snapshot.py -k creation_channel, but the 'legacy_snapshot' and 'snapshot_only' test functions in test_creation_channel_compaction.py are unassigned to any child AC — a partial-without-remainder gap.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9a72b21f040c5e3e","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87, Acceptance Criteria AC5 and AC3 vs. parent AC10","norm_id":"n0cb3b7d90d0addf4","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A test function named 'test_legacy_snapshot_*' or 'test_snapshot_only_*' in test_creation_channel_compaction.py could fail or be absent without any child AC detecting the gap, meaning the parent's completion verifier would catch a gap the children never promised to close.","If test_creation_channel_compaction.py's legacy-SNAPSHOT-fallback behavior is exercised only in test_reducer_snapshot.py (AC3), the higher-level end-to-end lifecycle file misses the corresponding test coverage, weakening the audit durability guarantee."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Expand child 568c AC5's -k selector from 'rebuild or horizon or rollback_recovery' to 'rebuild or horizon or rollback_recovery or legacy_snapshot or snapshot_only', OR add a dedicated AC in 568c: 'A pre-feature legacy SNAPSHOT and SNAPSHOT-only replay via test_creation_channel_compaction.py return the correct recorded/inferred/unknown projection. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k \"legacy_snapshot or snapshot_only\".'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Justify the placement of the downgrade runbook in `docs/concurrency.md`, or relocate the three-state schema matrix and compaction-pause procedure to a more discoverable home (e.g., `docs/operations.md` or a dedicated `docs/schema-rollback.md`) and update the AC proof commands accordingly.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"docs/concurrency.md defines the full-downgrade three-state schema matrix, the unconditional compaction pause, the affected-ID capture step, plus compensating-forward rebuild from retained .retired CREATE files.\"","No rationale is given in the plan for locating schema-rollback runbook content in a file named 'concurrency'.","ABSENCE: no pointer from docs/concurrency.md to an operations or deployment guide, and no mention of whether an existing operations/deployment doc already exists that would be a more natural home."],"finding":"The plan places the full-downgrade three-state schema matrix, compaction pause procedure, affected-ID capture step, and compensating-forward rebuild instructions in `docs/concurrency.md`, but no rationale is given for this placement. 'Concurrency' conventionally describes concurrent-access semantics, not schema rollback/downgrade runbooks. Operators and auditors looking for downgrade procedures are unlikely to search there, reducing the operational value of the otherwise well-specified rollback path.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2c0d882f9244379a","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — last two AC bullets; Architecture Decisions — rollback matrix paragraph","norm_id":"ndb06f32775a3ee59","priority":0.1237,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An operator performing an emergency downgrade searches docs/operations.md or docs/deployment.md (natural homes for runbook content) and misses the compaction-pause instruction, violating the pause and triggering the attribution-loss scenario the plan describes.","A new maintainer auditing the rollback procedure reads docs/concurrency.md and conflates schema-downgrade guidance with concurrent-writer semantics, causing confusion about scope."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Define a staged rollout path (e.g., a feature flag or explicit operator gate) so the new creation_channel writes can be enabled incrementally, OR document and test the exact rollback procedure (including the compaction-pause enforcement mechanism) as a first-class tested AC item — the current AC for docs/concurrency.md covers documentation but does not include a behavioral test of the pause enforcement or a smoke-test of the full rollback sequence.","cohort":["E3","T12"],"criteria":["T12"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"The MVP deliberately has no writer-only configuration switch or intermediate binary mode; attribution defects are recovered by pausing the affected creation ingress at the deployment boundary and rolling forward.\"","\"If that pause is violated, record affected IDs from the downgrade-window compaction activity, re-deploy the new binary, and rebuild those snapshots from the full log with rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log/include_retired\"","The plan acknowledges scheduled compaction operations ('stop every scheduled or manual rebar compact invocation'), confirming this is a deployed system with operational cadence."],"finding":"The plan explicitly adopts a single-binary-flip deployment with no staged rollout flag or canary path, and the rollback procedure is non-trivial (requires operator action to stop compaction, capture affected IDs, re-deploy, and rebuild snapshots) — failing T12(a) and making T12(b) only partially satisfied for a system with scheduled compaction operations.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9a0437a310680f31","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback matrix paragraph; Risks and Mitigations — 'Downgrade first-compaction omission'; AC — docs/concurrency.md item","norm_id":"nf300c04e49cea96a","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An operator deploys the new binary to a system with active scheduled compaction before verifying the pause is in place; the compaction pause is violated during a rollback window, producing SNAPSHOTs that omit creation_channel, requiring a non-trivial multi-step recovery.","A team with multiple deployment targets (e.g., CI runner + developer workstations) cannot gate the change to a subset of traffic without a feature flag."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add an AC item that tests the rollback recovery sequence end-to-end: deploy new binary, write some CREATE events, simulate a compaction-pause violation (run old-binary compaction), re-deploy new binary, call rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log, and assert creation_channel is correctly restored. This converts the documented three-state matrix into a tested, cheap rollback path. Alternatively, add a REBAR_CREATION_CHANNEL_ENABLED environment flag so the new field can be deployed to a subset of processes before enabling writes universally.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Explicitly state that `rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log` is idempotent per ticket (safe to re-run on an already-rebuilt SNAPSHOT) and describe how a partially-completed multi-ticket rebuild can be resumed without double-applying or skipping any ticket (e.g., by checking whether the SNAPSHOT already contains a non-unknown `creation_channel` before rebuilding).","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'re-deploy the new binary, and rebuild those snapshots from the full log with rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log/include_retired'","'Story 568c adds a regression for that compensating-forward recovery'","No mention of idempotency or partial-restart safety for the rebuild across multiple tickets"],"finding":"The compensating-forward rebuild step (`rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log` over 'affected IDs') is the sole stated recovery path after a violated compaction-pause, but the plan never asserts this operation is idempotent or resumable if interrupted mid-run across a large set of tickets.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f95809d484a03e983","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback matrix; Risks and Mitigations — 'Downgrade first-compaction omission'","norm_id":"n2e42477cab322fa6","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A large deployment with thousands of tickets undergoes a violated compaction pause; the rebuild run crashes partway through; re-running it either reprocesses already-fixed tickets (harmless only if idempotent) or skips them (losing provenance for a subset)"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence in the rollback matrix section: 'rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log is idempotent: if a SNAPSHOT already reflects a non-unknown creation_channel derived from the retained CREATE, the rebuild is a no-op for that ticket, making a partial-run safe to restart without tracking per-ticket completion state.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify a concrete mechanism for capturing 'affected IDs' during a violated compaction-pause window (e.g., 'scan the compaction activity log / SNAPSHOT mtime for the downgrade window', or 'run `rebar compact --dry-run --since=<downgrade-ts>` to enumerate tickets compacted without creation_channel') so that the rebuild step can be applied exhaustively rather than relying on manual recall.","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'record affected IDs from the downgrade-window compaction activity, re-deploy the new binary, and rebuild those snapshots'","No description of how 'affected IDs' are captured — no log query, no compaction audit trail, no tooling reference","DATA LOSS RISK: if the affected-ID list is incomplete, some tickets remain with provenance-stripped SNAPSHOTs indefinitely"],"finding":"The plan instructs operators to 'record affected IDs from the downgrade-window compaction activity' but provides no mechanism or tooling for reliably capturing that set; missed IDs would be silently left with provenance-stripped SNAPSHOTs — a DATA LOSS RISK for audit integrity.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fadaa6f46bc524fad","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback matrix; AC — 'Story 568c adds a regression for that compensating-forward recovery'","norm_id":"na6cbfe322115620f","priority":0.099,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Operator performs emergency downgrade; old binary compacts N tickets concurrently before the pause is applied; operator reconstructs only a partial list of affected IDs from memory or ad-hoc log search; remaining tickets are left with creation_channel-free SNAPSHOTs that the new binary cannot distinguish from legitimately-unknown tickets"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify that `_project_legacy_creation_channel` is a REDUCER-side projection function (called from within the `process_create` or `_replay` path), not placed inside `inbound_translate._event_meta` (a write-side event-metadata factory); update the Architecture Decisions section to name the correct read-side host module and call site.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py lines 158-168: `def _event_meta() -> tuple[int, str, str, str]: ... return (_time.time_ns(), str(_uuid.uuid4()), _rebar_env('ENV_ID', 'reconciler'), _rebar_env('AUTHOR', 'reconciler'))`","Plan states: 'inbound_translate._event_meta performs the absolute package import ... following the module's established late-import pattern' — but the existing late-import pattern in _event_meta is for `time` and `uuid` only (write-side concerns)","Legacy Jira inference is a reducer projection concern (read-side), not a write-side concern — it evaluates existing stored events, not new ones being written"],"finding":"The plan assigns `_project_legacy_creation_channel` (a reducer read-side decision rule) to `inbound_translate._event_meta`, which is confirmed by code inspection to be a write-side factory function that returns (timestamp_ns, uuid4_str, env_id, author) for new events. The late-import pattern cited ('following the module's established late-import pattern') in _event_meta refers to importing `time` and `uuid` — not reducer constants. Placing legacy inference logic inside a write-side helper is a structural mis-location that could cause the inference to run on the wrong side of the event boundary.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f736cf491d293c78b","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section — 'inbound_translate._event_meta performs the absolute package import (from rebar.reducer._version import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID) inside its function body'","norm_id":"n33bc9618bae82b50","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementor places `_project_legacy_creation_channel` inside `_event_meta`, which only runs during new event creation — legacy historical events are never re-evaluated by this path","The import `from rebar.reducer._version import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID` inside `_event_meta` creates a circular dependency risk (reconciler importing from rebar.reducer at write time rather than at read/reduce time)"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Place `_project_legacy_creation_channel` in `src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` (called from `process_create` when no concrete `creation_channel` is present) or `src/rebar/reducer/_replay.py`; the `inbound_translate._event_meta` sentence should be removed or replaced with a statement that the Jira inference runs in the reducer.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Either add a `\"const\"` handler to `gen_types._pytype()` that emits `Literal[True]` for `{\"const\": true}`, or encode `creation_channel_inferred` as `{\"type\": \"boolean\", \"enum\": [true]}` so the existing `enum` handler fires; document the chosen approach in the Architecture Decisions.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py lines 115-149: `_pytype()` handles `$ref`, `enum`, array, object, scalar — no `const` branch; `jtype is None` returns `Any`","Plan states the schema encoding is `{\"const\": true}` and that the gen_types check must pass","The `--check` command only verifies the generated file matches re-generation output — it does NOT verify the generated type is semantically `Literal[True]`; it would pass with `Any`"],"finding":"The plan encodes `creation_channel_inferred` as `{\"const\": true}` in `ticket_state.schema.json` and asserts `python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check` will pass (AC7), but `gen_types._pytype()` has no handler for the `\"const\"` keyword. Confirmed by reading `gen_types.py` lines 115-149: the method handles `$ref`, `enum`, array/object/scalar types — `const` falls through to the `jtype is None` branch returning `Any`. The generated type for `creation_channel_inferred` would be `NotRequired[Any]` rather than `NotRequired[Literal[True]]`.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f55f0f2f91f1bb6d1","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'ticket_state.schema.json encodes that rule formally as {\"const\": true}'; AC7 — 'Prove with ... python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check'","norm_id":"na6e816bbed667d5e","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["gen_types regenerates types.py with `creation_channel_inferred: NotRequired[Any]` instead of `NotRequired[Literal[True]]`; the --check AC passes because the generated output matches the stale file","Type-checkers and consumers receive `Any` for the inference marker, defeating its diagnostic value"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In `gen_types._pytype()`, add before the `jtype = node.get('type')` line: `if 'const' in node: self._used_typing.add('Literal'); return f\"Literal[{node['const']!r}]\"`. Alternatively, encode the schema field as `{\"enum\": [true]}` to reuse the existing `enum` branch.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Make the Architecture Decisions section explicit that 'written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides' means 'the stored author or env_id value does not equal LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR or LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID respectively' — not a runtime env-var check — and that this falls out naturally from the three-signal predicate failing.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py lines 166-167: `_rebar_env('ENV_ID', 'reconciler'), _rebar_env('AUTHOR', 'reconciler')` — default values are 'reconciler', same as LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR/LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID","Plan does not define 'written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides' — the stored event author/env_id would equal whatever the env var was set to at write time, not a flag that the var was overridden","If REBAR_AUTHOR was overridden to 'reconciler' (the default), the event is indistinguishable from a default-written event; if overridden to something else, the three-signal predicate fails on the author check — but the plan never makes this chain explicit"],"finding":"The plan states 'Missing/None signals or legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides intentionally project unknown' but never specifies what REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID override values trigger the `unknown` branch versus the three-signal `jira` inference. The env vars have a default of 'reconciler' (confirmed from `inbound_translate.py` line 166-167), making them coincide with `LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR`/`LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID`. The plan does not define when a non-default env-var override counts as a disqualifying signal.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc2702e81a6a684b5","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Missing/None signals or legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides intentionally project unknown'","norm_id":"n29767ff50cd0eca0","priority":0.1414,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A deployment sets REBAR_AUTHOR=custom-reconciler; historical events written then have author='custom-reconciler', which fails the LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR check and correctly projects unknown — but the plan's 'REBAR_AUTHOR override' language is opaque about this being the mechanism","A future implementor adds a check for whether REBAR_AUTHOR was explicitly set, rather than checking the stored author value, and produces the wrong result"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Replace 'legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides' with 'legacy events whose stored author ≠ LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR or stored env_id ≠ LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID' to make the decision rule self-contained and unambiguous.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Document and enforce that each story's additions to tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py cover only the documentation content that story itself introduces, so the test file is always in a passing state after each sequential story lands.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["e622 AC8: 'Prove with uv run pytest -q ... tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && make lint'","568c AC7: 'Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && make lint'","568c is the 'final documentation integrator' per its AC7, adding SNAPSHOT placement, actor/environment/source_* distinctions, and rollback documentation assertions to test_schema_coverage.py","If 568c's SNAPSHOT-placement assertions are present in test_schema_coverage.py before 568c's documentation additions exist, e622's CI run (which runs test_schema_coverage.py) would fail","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Child e622 explicitly scopes OUT 'executing SNAPSHOT-only legacy inference' from its delivery but child 568c's scope-in description says it will call _project_legacy_creation_channel from process_snapshot — however, e622's own verify commands (AC8) run tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py, which the parent's AC13/14 also rely on. If 568c extends test_schema_coverage.py with SNAPSHOT-placement or rollback-matrix assertions that are meant to be proved only after 568c lands, but those assertions are also exercised in e622's verify suite (because e622 runs the same test file), then e622's CI could fail awaiting 568c content — an implicit shared-state ordering risk across the two children's test_schema_coverage.py contributions.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa92f46925dadbfce","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 AC8 and child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 AC7, both running tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py","norm_id":"n31aee825fcf48ab9","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Developer writes 568c's test_schema_coverage.py extensions early (e.g., on the feature branch during e622 work) covering SNAPSHOT-placement content that only 568c's docs/ additions will satisfy — e622 CI fails because the test_schema_coverage.py on the branch already asserts 568c content.","The test_schema_coverage.py is a shared file incrementally extended by all three stories; if the branch strategy is not carefully managed, later-story test additions can pre-empt earlier-story CI green checks."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a note to the decomposition or branch strategy: each story's PR may only extend test_schema_coverage.py with assertions that the same PR's docs/ changes satisfy. 568c's SNAPSHOT-placement and rollback-matrix assertions must not appear in the test file before 568c's docs/event-schema.md, docs/output-schemas.md, and docs/concurrency.md additions land.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":["ISF"],"criteria":["ISF"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Session log ticket graph: 'links: - relates_to -> 52f0-f43c-834b-430e'","The plan text contains no mention of ticket 52f0-f43c-834b-430e, no rationale for dropping the link, and no instruction to implementers to record or maintain this relationship."],"finding":"The plan silently drops the 'relates_to -> 52f0-f43c-834b-430e' link expressed in the session log's ticket graph without stating any rationale for the omission.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f935621705cac1ecd","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"n68fad8e4f3af5687","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["The relates_to relationship is never recorded in the shared store, leaving the audit trail incomplete and auditors unaware of the associated context.","If 52f0-f43c-834b-430e contains constraints or decisions that inform creation_channel provenance, implementers have no signal to consult it.","Post-implementation review cannot verify the relationship exists, violating the ticket graph as expressed by the user."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.0833,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"insufficient","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"insufficient","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan asserts creation_channel is immutable after genesis ('Reducer processors treat creation_channel as CREATE/SNAPSHOT-only state and ignore the key on every later mutation event'), but the existing process_edit in _processors.py applies any field already in state when it appears in EDIT.fields (line 494: `if field_name not in state: continue`). Since process_create will add creation_channel (and conditionally creation_channel_inferred) to state, a subsequent EDIT event containing fields.creation_channel will silently overwrite genesis provenance. The plan never specifies that process_edit must have an explicit named exclusion for these keys — only that mutation events 'ignore the key', which is true for specialized processors (LINK, STATUS, JIRA_BIND) but is NOT automatically true for the general-purpose process_edit without an explicit guard.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2bb5fda9fe912bdd","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section ('Reducer processors treat creation_channel as CREATE/SNAPSHOT-only state and ignore the key on every later mutation event'); src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py lines 485-510","norm_id":"n4289d61664b4bf81","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In _processors.py, add a module-level frozenset: `_IMMUTABLE_FIELDS = frozenset({'creation_channel', 'creation_channel_inferred'})` and add `if field_name in _IMMUTABLE_FIELDS: continue` inside the process_edit loop before the general assignment. Reference this constant from the plan's Architecture Decisions section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G4","G3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"Child 6fe2 AC4 claims that 'a legacy CREATE with no channel reduces to unknown without creation_channel_inferred,' implying the reducer writes creation_channel=unknown into compiled state. Child e622 defines _project_legacy_creation_channel as 'a no-op when state already has creation_channel.' If 6fe2's reducer sets creation_channel=unknown for missing-field legacy CREATEs, e622's helper will always be a no-op for those records, blocking Jira inference from ever firing on full-log replay. The two children cannot both be correct as written: either 6fe2 sets unknown (which blocks e622's inference) or 6fe2 leaves the field absent (which means 6fe2 AC4's 'reduces to unknown' is not verifiable at 6fe2's own delivery boundary, before e622 exists).","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f93e1c06c2f62b2e4","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 AC4; child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 What (_project_legacy_creation_channel no-op guard)","norm_id":"nae1fde64f234f78e","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Define the contract explicitly: 6fe2's reducer does NOT write creation_channel into compiled_state when the CREATE event has no creation_channel field (i.e., field remains absent from state dict). e622's _project_legacy_creation_channel is the sole writer for legacy records (setting jira+inferred on match, unknown on mismatch). Update 6fe2 AC4 to say 'a legacy CREATE with no channel is left without creation_channel until the inference helper runs, which then projects unknown for non-Jira records without an inferred marker.' This keeps the no-op guard meaningful (it guards against re-inference of already-resolved state, including recorded channels and post-e622 unknown outputs).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"7b1bd8ff567a87e1","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":278.7,"llm_calls":23,"llm_ms":374964.3,"total_ms":375371.6,"verify_requests":19},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"jira-reb-977","ticket_type":"epic","verdict":"PASS","verified_at_sha":"faa40e7b07b1ebfd7f0a12e122e9017b0cdd0b35"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784268379486387001,"uuid":"b6ac34b4-c7e3-40d5-b2b9-ca2aa80cd677"}